issue.title: JS loader file
issue.body: Create JS file that reads Data.txt and loads the data onto the html document(index.html)

issue.title: Merge index.html with JS files
issue.body: Do at the end. Merge all the programs so that index.html functions properly

issue.title: write zom_main.py
issue.body: This is the main part of the program. Edit the zom_main.py file to take all the previous files (all the Calc.py files as well as outbreaklocation.txt and places.txt) and evaluate the scores of all locations. It will write the info(score for each category and overall score as well as name, location and type) of the top 5 areas to a file called Data.txt

issue.title: Create JS file to get the outbreak location
issue.body: Create a JS file that interacts with index.html so that after the webpage has loaded, the user can click on the map and drop a pin representing the outbreak location. This location (lng and lat) is written to a file called outbreaklocation.txt.

issue.title: Python Initialiser file

issue.title: Loading screen?
issue.body: If there is time, create a loading screen overlay. When not loading set the opacity of the overlay to 0(make it invisible). Anytime we do some calculation set the opacity to 100

issue.title: Density Calculator ?
issue.body: If there is time, investigate the four square api, to calculate how dense a location is. Create a new file called densCalc.py containing all the functions neccesarry.

issue.title: Elevation Calculator
issue.body: Study example in working dir, work in elevCalc.py to write all fuctions for calculating a score between 0 - 100 for the elevation of a location.

issue.title: Distance Calculator
issue.body: write in distCalc.py, all functions for distance calculation. The function will also take a lng and lat for the outbreak location. If a zombie can get to the location faster than you can walk, the score of the location is instantly 0. Determine score for distance between 0-100 and return it.

issue.title: Food calculation
issue.body:
Create a seperate .py file (foodCalc.py) that contains all functions necessary to calculate the food score from 0 - 100.
Factors to consider:
- Select from the list of types all types that may have food eg supermarket
- Rank list of types in order of how much food each will have
- Use info about reviews and pricing to calculate food quality and quantity
         - high number of reviews and low prices means lots of supply
         - review score and price determine quality
